SYMS MERNS-Stephen. With broken heart and loving affection, my sad goodbye. Lynn Syms

SYMS MERNS-Stephen. The Yeshiva University family is deeply saddened by the untimely passing of an esteemed businessman and member of the Jewish community, beloved husband of Karen; father of Jillian, Daniel, and Olivia; son of Sy Syms and Ruth Merns; and brother of Marcy Syms Merns, Laura, Adrienne, Robert, and Richard. Stephen's family is deeply involved with Yeshiva University. His mother and father are each YU Benefactors; his father, Sy, is vice chairman of the YU Board of Trustees, an honorary alumnus, and eponym of our Sy Syms School of Business. Marcy Syms Merns, like her father a member of the SSSB Board, established the Marcy Syms Scholarship there. We extend our heartfelt condolences to the entire family. May they be comforted among the mourners of Zion and Jerusalem. Dr. Norman Lamm, President Yeshiva University David S. Gottesman, Chairman Board of Trustees Josh S. Weston, Chairman SSSB Board of Directors Dr. Harold Nierenberg, Dean SSSB

SYMS MERNS-Stephen. Gone is the joy of our hearts, our dancing has turned into mourning (Lamentations 5:15). Boys Town Jerusalem mourns with profound sorrow the tragic and untimely passing of Stephen Syms Merns, son of cherished members of our extended family, Sy Syms and Ruth Merns. We pray that Stephen's family will find some measure of comfort knowing that the major scholarship endowment, established by Sy Syms, Chai Founder of Boys Town, will indeed provide the gift of life to disadvantaged Israeli youth by offering them hope and opportunity. ''Never again shall your sun set....and ended shall be the days of your mourning'' (Isaiah 60:20). Our heartfelt condolences to the entire family. Josh S. Weston, Chairman Michael J. Scharf, President Rabbi Moshe Linchner, Vice Chairman Rabbi Ronald L. Gray, Executive Vice President

SYMS MERNS-Stephen. The Leadership and Staff of State of Israel Bonds were deeply shocked and saddened to learn of the untimely and tragic passing of Stephen Syms Merns. His commitment to Israel and the Jewish community continued a tradition begun by his father, Sy Syms, former chairman of the Board of Israel Bonds; his mother, Ruth Merns, a member of the North American Women's Division Board; and his sister, Marcy Syms Merns, former chairperson of the Greater New York Campaign, cherished members of the Israel Bonds extended family. Our heartfelt condolences to his family. May they be comforted among the mourners of Zion. Gideon Patt, President and CEO Burton P. Resnick, Chairman of the Board Irwin Hochberg, National Campaign Chairman Howard Hirsch, Campaign Chairman, Greater New York

SYMS MERNS-Stephen. The Officers, Board of Directors, and staff of UJA-Federation of New York mourn the passing of Stephen Merns Syms, an ardent supporter of the Jewish community who emulated his family's concern for the welfare and survival of the Jewish people. We extend our sincerest condolences to his beloved wife, Karen; his children, Jillian, Daniel and Olivia; his father, Sy Syms; his mother, Ruth Merns; his sisters, Marcy, Laura and Adrienne; and his brothers, Robert and Richard. Judith Stern Peck, Board Chair James S. Tisch, President Stephen D. Solender, Exec. VP